A man pulled a pistol on his friends and opened fire, killing one and critically wounding another, in a dispute over beer money, a court heard.

Gumaro Torres has been charged with first-degree murder, attempted first-degree murder and aggravated battery with a deadly weapon over the shootings in Chicago, Illinois.

The 31-year-old is being held with no bail after the fatal incident on the 1800 block of North Pulaski Road, in Chicago's Hermosa neighbourhood, late last Friday night.

