Prosecutors allege that Torres was sitting drinking around a picnic table in the back yard of a home with a group of others when he began to get angry at getting no change from his beer money.

An argument broke out and after a short while the suspect is alleged to have left the group and gone to his nearby home before returning with a loaded 9mm semi-automatic hand gun.

'He stated that he was angry that when he returned the victims laughed at him,' prosecutors told the court.

Incensed, he 'immediately began to fire his gun at Jose De LaFuente,' prosecutors were quoted by the Chicago Tribune as saying.

Mr De LaFuente, 35, was shot in the abdomen and died at Mount Sinai Hospital at 2.45am on Saturday morning.

