Another friend tried to tackle Torres but, as he approached, was shot in the hand, abdomen, leg and right hip.

The injured 27-year-old remains in a critical condition at the Advocate Illinois Masonic Medical Center.

A third man was able to subdue Torres, but not before suffering several 'pistol whips' in the head with the butt of the pistol.

He was treated at the scene and released.

